				<h4 class="font-size-18"><b>3. Is a Thesis Required?</b></h4>
				<p>All Yenching Scholars are required to write a Master's thesis under the guidance of a faculty adviser, and to defend it orally before an academic committee.</p>
				<h4 class="font-size-18"><b>4. What Kind of Dormitory Rooms Will Be Provided?</b></h4>
				<p>Yenching Scholars will be housed in updated, single rooms in an existing dormitory on campus. </p>
				<h4 class="font-size-18"><b>5. When Will Information Be Available on the Curriculum?</b></h4>
				<p>The curriculum, which will consist of a set of core, obligatory courses as well as an array of electives, is currently under development.  More information will be available on this site mid-autumn. </p>	
				<h4 class="font-size-18"><b>6. When Will the Faculty Be Appointed?</b></h4>
				<p>Faculty will be seconded from existing schools and departments of Peking University (PKU), as well as recruited from outside.  Announcements of faculty appointments will be made on a rolling basis. Please check back on this website for further information.</p>
